										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span class="paragraph">The Tomato Bruschetta, is a typical appetizer of Italian cuisine. Is known throughout Italy as a starter, prepared in many different versions. It is a very popular snack before meals or between courses.</span></p>
<p>Easy, tasty and strictly <a class="underline" title="Mediterranean cuisine" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediterranean_cuisine">Mediterranean!</a></p>
<h2>Enjoy our Tomato Bruschetta</h2>

    
<div class="lt-recipe" id="lt-recipe" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Recipe">
    <h4 itemprop="name">Toasted Bread with Tomatoes (Bruschetta)</h4>
        <div class="recipe-info">
                    <div class="publish-date"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="March 18, 2017">March 18, 2017</div> 
                            <div class="servings"><i class="fa fa-user"></i> <label>Servings</label>: 4-6</div>
                                                <div class="difficulty"><i class="fa fa-tachometer"></i> <label>Difficulty</label>: Easy</div>
            </div>
            <div class="recipe-print">
        <a href="javascript:kale_print_recipe('lt-recipe');"><i class="fa fa-print"></i> Print This</a>
    </div>
            <p class="recipe-summary" itemprop="description">The Bruschetta (Toasted Bread with Tomatoes) is a typical appetizer of Italian cuisine. Is known throughout Italy as a starter, prepared in many different versions. It is a very popular snack before meals or between courses. Easy, tasty and strictly Mediterranean! Enjoy our Bruschetta</p>
        <p class="recipe-author">By: <span itemprop="author">italianpot</span></p>
        <div class="recipe-image"><img decoding="async" itemprop="image" src="http://italianpot.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/bruschetta-02.jpg" alt="Tomato Bruschetta" class="img-responsive" /></div>
        <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-5"><div class="recipe-ingredients">
        <h5>Ingredients</h5>
        <ul>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">Bread 2 Slice of Italian Bread per person</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">1/2 lb. Tomatoes diced</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">fresh Basil</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">2-3 cloves Garlic</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">1/2 c. Olive Oil</li>
                        <li itemprop="recipeIngredient">1 Pinch Hot Pepper</li>
                    </ul>
    </div></div>
            <div class="col-md-7"><div class="recipe-directions">
        <h5>Directions</h5>
        <ul itemprop="recipeInstructions">
                        <li><span class="step">Step 1</span> Put diced tomatoes into a bowl with olive oil, garlic, hot pepper, basil and salt.</li>
                        <li><span class="step">Step 2</span> Mix well.</li>
                        <li><span class="step">Step 3</span> Slice bread 1/2â€³ thick and toast both sides.</li>
                        <li><span class="step">Step 4</span> Remove from toaster and place on serving tray.</li>
                        <li><span class="step">Step 5</span> Place an equal portion of tomato mixture on each slice.</li>
                        <li><span class="step">Step 6</span> Serve immediately.</li>
                    </ul>
    </div></div>
        </div>
</div>
